{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-iso3166-mus"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Independent Public-Sector Market-Entry & Procurement Compliance Service — Mauritius"
 :itonami.blueprint/iso3166 "MUS"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :public-sector/market-entry-compliance
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :market-entry-compliance-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics false
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:identity :forms :dmn :bpmn :audit-ledger]
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "src/marketentry/{facts,governor,store,registry,marketentryllm,operation,phase,sim}.cljc
  -- MarketEntry-LLM (mock advisor) sealed behind a langgraph-clj
  StateGraph (intake -> advise -> govern -> decide -> [request-approval] ->
  commit|hold), censored by a 7-check Market-Entry Compliance Governor
  (spec-basis, evidence-incomplete, cbris-registration-missing [flagship],
  engagement-fee-mismatch, eprocurement-registration-unverified,
  confidence-floor/actuation-gate, already-drafted/already-submitted),
  Store protocol with MemStore + DatomicStore (built on
  io.github.kotoba-lang/langchain-store, not a hand-rolled enc/dec*
  codec), 0->3 phase rollout gate, and an append-only audit ledger.
  `:filing/draft`/`:filing/submit` never auto-commit at any phase.
  Facts catalog (src/marketentry/facts.cljc) is grounded exclusively in
  the verified MUS dossier: PPO (Procurement Policy Office,
  https://ppo.govmu.org/), Public Procurement Act 2006 (Act 33 of
  2006), the PPO e-Procurement System (mandatory registration since 28
  September 2015, https://publicprocurement.govmu.org/), and the
  Corporate and Business Registration Department (CBRD) via the
  Corporate and Business Registration Integrated System (CBRIS --
  Certificate of Incorporation + Business Registration Number). Test
  suite: test/marketentry/{facts,governor_contract,store_contract,
  registry,phase}_test.clj -- one test per governor rule, MemStore ≡
  DatomicStore parity, pure-function registry coverage, and full
  StateGraph end-to-end exercise for both a commit path
  (clean-intake-auto-commits) and a hold path
  (fabricated-jurisdiction-is-held / the 4 HARD-hold rule tests)."}
